Package radin.core.semantics.types

Class CXType

java.lang.Object
radin.core.semantics.types.CXType
All Implemented Interfaces:
CXEquivalent
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractCXPrimitiveType, ConstantType, CXCompoundType, CXCompoundTypeNameIndirection, CXDynamicTypeDefinition, CXGenericType, CXGenericTypeInstance, CXMappedType, CXNamespacedType
public abstract class CXType
extends Object
implements CXEquivalent
Base treeType for any CXType. This needs to be inherited for a treeType to be properly tracked Represents all C Types and Class Types

    • is

      public abstract boolean is​(CXType other, TypeEnvironment e, boolean strictPrimitiveEquality)
      Same as is(CXType, TypeEnvironment), except with the ability to determine whether to use strict boolean equality TypeEnvironment.isStrict(CXType, CXType) is preferred, as it properly unwraps types that need to be unwrapped
      Parameters:

      e - the treeType environment to check in
      strictPrimitiveEquality - Uses a more strict treeType check for primitives CXPrimitiveType.is(CXType, TypeEnvironment, boolean)
      Returns:
      where this object treeType "strictly is" another treeType

      public boolean isExact​(CXType other, TypeEnvironment e)
